values.summary:
Support the servers, network, workstations, and other IT infrastructure of multiple clients in Cookeville and the surrounding area. This includes a wide range of skills, from setting up a new domain controller with a Distributed File System over a VPN to troubleshooting a network connection on an IP camera, or cleaning a malware infected workstation.

Wrote multiple PowerShell scripts to automate time consuming and reoccurring assignments. One of these scripts assigns granular permissions to 125 users on 28 folders based on a user matrix updated by the client. This script sets 3500 permissions in about 30 seconds.

Server experience includes: setup of physical and virtual servers (on both Hyper-V and ESXi); Windows Server 2003, 2008, and 2012; managing Active Directory in multiple environments; managing Exchange Server 2008; PowerShell scripting; installation and maintenance of server centralized applications; and backup operations.

Workstation experience includes: Windows XP, 7, and 8 support; application support; communication troubleshooting (network, printers, etc.); hardware related troubleshooting and upgrades; and virus/malware removal.

Network experience includes: wired and wireless infrastructure planning, installation, and support; switch programming and installation; router and firewall programming with emphasis on VPN connectivity.

Help many individuals with their various technical issues over the phone, in remote sessions, and in person, striving to build the reputation and trust for the company through my communication, helpfulness, and disposition.
